  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients who present for the first time to Emergency Room with renal colic due to a distal
      ureteral calculus (as diagnosed with spiral CT scan and KUB) will be randomized to receive
      Xatral 10mg po once a day or placebo once discharged from the ER. The purpose of this study
      is to assess if patients treated with Xatral will have a higher spontaneous passage rate of
      their ureteral stone than those treated with placebo.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
